snippet.textDisplay: It would be a bit better if you had a few small portable tanks (with some kind of strap) and bigger tanks of helium, along with some balloons and string. It would be a better way to prolong the game, each player could only have a set amount of balloons to prevent if from being too OP (except for Mr. five-balloons), and it would simulate the bit in the game where you can actually heal. Though it would be tedious and not very practical in a fight situation to heal in such a way, you could use editing to make it look doable. Being able to revive a fallen teammate a couple seconds after they die would make it more interesting, sure. But there's just no way to implement this. IF you make a part 2, please at least consider this. Though I wouldn't suggest making a part 2 too soon, just maybe hint at it to raise hype, and prolong it to make sure everything is planned out. This WAS well scripted and entertaining though as is, just thought I might add a couple pointers for those that are eager for new ideas.
